   A subsidiary of London-based Tate &amp; Lyle PLC, is expected
to announce as early as today that it has received approval
of the Canadian government to market a new calorie-free sugar
replacement called sucralose.
   The new sugar replacer, which will be sold world-wide
under the brand name Splenda, is three times sweeter than
best selling NutraSweet, and contains zero calories. The
substance is the only one of its type derived from common
table sugar. Also unlike NutraSweet, the brand name for
aspartame, sucralose can be used at high temperatures in
