<TEXT>
   Genex Corp. said it agreed with Monsanto Co.'s NutraSweet unit to settle a two-year-old lawsuit connected to NutraSweet's decision to stop buying raw material for its aspartame sweetener from the biotechnology research firm. 
Under the settlement, in which the companies agreed to release each other from all claims, Gaithersburg, Md.-based Genex plans to reverse a previously recorded liability of $1.4 million, which will be reflected as earnings in the third quarter. 
In the 1986 third quarter, Genex had a net loss of $961,000. 

